Scan target for open ports and identify services running on them.

Basic Nmap Scan
bash
# Scan legal test target 
nmap scanme.nmap.org

Example Scan Results
text
PORT    STATE SERVICE
22/tcp  open  ssh     # Secure Shell (remote login)
80/tcp  open  http    # Web server (HTTP)
9929/tcp open  nping-echo # Nmap testing service

Common Open Ports Explained
Port	Service	Purpose
22/tcp	SSH	Secure remote login/administration
80/tcp	HTTP	Web server (unencrypted websites)
443/tcp	HTTPS	Secure web server (SSL/TLS)
21/tcp	FTP	File transfer protocol
3306/tcp	MySQL	Database server
Scan Commands
bash
# Quick scan (top 1000 ports)
nmap scanme.nmap.org

# Specific ports
nmap -p 22,80,443 scanme.nmap.org

# All ports (65k - takes time!)
nmap -p- scanme.nmap.org

# Service version detection
nmap -sV scanme.nmap.org
Output Legend
text
PORT     STATE  SERVICE
22/tcp   open   ssh      ✅ Service listening
80/tcp   closed http     ❌ No service
111/tcp  filtered rpcbind ❓ Firewall blocking
Legal Test Target
Use only: scanme.nmap.org (Nmap official test server)

bash
nmap scanme.nmap.org
# Always shows ports 22, 80, 9929 open

-sV = Detect service versions
-p- = Scan all 65,535 ports
-F = Fast scan (top 100 ports)

-T4 = Faster timing
